<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hiss2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hiss,</orth> vb. 1) intr. to utter a noise like a serpent: <bibl n="shak. ven 17" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 871" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 871</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.5.124" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 5, 124</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.935" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 935</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 1, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 3, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 17</bibl> (Ff <emph>hizzing</emph>). With an accus. denoting the effect: <cit><quote>h. me into madness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 14</bibl></cit>. Expressing contempt and disapprobation: <bibl n="shak. lll 5.1.145" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 1, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.10.55" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 10, 55</bibl>. With <cit><quote>at:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 1, 78</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) tr. to condemn by hissing, to explode: <bibl n="shak. ven 1084" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1084</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.189" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 189</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.1.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 1, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.261" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 261</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 4.3.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. IV, 3, 175</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>